Variables and Data Types
variable -  are the container that store some reusable data.

![Untitled](https://prod-files-secure.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/259a8645-34fe-4ab2-a2bb-e37dd3a6e8f4/515fe433-4caf-4ccd-b5d9-bf0c51bd978d/Untitled.png)

![Untitled](https://prod-files-secure.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/259a8645-34fe-4ab2-a2bb-e37dd3a6e8f4/da25f9ba-0903-49b0-bc63-8be209c19985/Untitled.png)

to declare variable use  -  “var” keyword

```
//syntax 
var Variablesname = 18;
```

now there are two different way to define variables after ES6 .

by 

- let

```jsx
let varName = "hello Wolrd!";

```

![Untitled](https://prod-files-secure.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/259a8645-34fe-4ab2-a2bb-e37dd3a6e8f4/c06c3d9d-a2e4-4550-bf71-f658be9a5c25/Untitled.png)

variable made using let can change value of it.

```jsx
let varName = "hello Wolrd!";
varName  = 19;
```

![Untitled](https://prod-files-secure.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/259a8645-34fe-4ab2-a2bb-e37dd3a6e8f4/75919465-9c6e-44cf-8a22-b695dc3a578a/Untitled.png)

- const
you cant change the value of variable using const beacuse it is constant .

```jsx
const varName = "hello Wolrd!";
varName  = 19;
console.log(varName);
```

![Untitled](https://prod-files-secure.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/259a8645-34fe-4ab2-a2bb-e37dd3a6e8f4/98a57c50-90d3-4b50-badf-e58f6a9f9dc9/Untitled.png)

you cant declare variable with same name again

```jsx
const varName = "hello Wolrd!";
const varName = "hello Wolrd!";

```

![Untitled](https://prod-files-secure.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/259a8645-34fe-4ab2-a2bb-e37dd3a6e8f4/04825adc-79e2-448d-9059-7b79347f9fa4/Untitled.png)

you name variable wiht lexical bound names.

```jsx
let var = "umang";
console.log(var);
```

![Untitled](https://prod-files-secure.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/259a8645-34fe-4ab2-a2bb-e37dd3a6e8f4/974018b9-56f5-4008-ab01-0adf6a80e8bc/Untitled.png)

variable start with only - alphabet, 

but can start with special char or number 

```jsx
//variables
var fname = "Umang";
let mname = "Arvindbhai";
const lname = "Raval";
```

