## Comments

```jsx
//single line comments
// for shard description of any code
```

```jsx
/*
  mullti line comments
*/
```

## String

there are three types of  string

you cn declare by

- “  “ double quotes
- ‘ ‘ single quotes
- ` `   back tick

```jsx
const exlstring = "hello world";
console.log(exlstring);
```

```jsx
//string
// all the thing between " " double quoute is called string
const singleQuote = 'Hello';
const doubleQuote = 'Hello';

//backtic
const fname = "uamng";
const backticks  = `Hello , ${fname}  , welcome`;
console.log(backticks)

//also to do maths
console.log(`${2+2}`)
```

![Untitled](https://prod-files-secure.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/259a8645-34fe-4ab2-a2bb-e37dd3a6e8f4/0d61a020-27b8-4e3d-b0e4-167b52e4c4f8/Untitled.png)

to check datatype sof any variable use  

- “  typeof “command to see datatypes

```jsx
const fname = "uamng";
const backticks  = `Hello , ${fname}  , welcome`;
console.log(typeof backticks)
```

